<sect id="authors">Who wrote this FAQ?

<p>Primary authors of the &debian; FAQ are Susan G. Kleinmann
(<email/sgk@debian.org/), Sven Rudolph (<email/sr1@inf.tu-dresden.de/),
and Joost Witteveen (<email/joostje@debian.org/).

<p>The FAQ was previously maintained by J.H.M. Dassen (Ray),
(<email/jdassen@wi.LeidenUniv.nl/), Chuck Stickelman
(<email/stick@richnet.net/), and Santiago Vila Dolcel (<email/sanvila@ctv.es/).
Current maintainer is Josip Rodin (<email/jrodin@jagor.srce.hr/).

<p>Parts of the information came from:
<list>
  <item>The Debian-1.1 release announcement, by Bruce Perens.
  <item>The <url name="Linux FAQ" id="http://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/users/iwj10/linux-faq/">
    by <url name="Ian Jackson" id="http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~ijackson/">,
  <item><url name="Debian Mailing Lists Archives" id="http://www.debian.org/Lists-Archives/">,
  <item>the dpkg programmers' manual and the Debian Policy manual
    (see <ref id="debiandocs">)
  <item>many developers, volunteers, and beta testers, and
  <item>the flaky memories of its authors. :-)
</list>

<p>The authors would like to thank all those who helped make this
document possible.

<sect id="feedback">Where do I send questions, corrections, etc. about
  this document?

<p>Comments on this document are welcome. Please send e-mail to
<email/doc-debian@packages.debian.org/, or better, submit a wishlist bug
report against the <package/doc-debian/ package.

<sect id="latest">Where do I get the latest version of this document?
	
<p>The latest version of this document can be viewed in HTML format at
the <url name="Debian home page" id="http://www.debian.org/doc/FAQ/">.

<p>It is also available in HTML, PostScript, .dvi and plain text format at
the <url name="Debian FTP server" id="ftp://ftp.debian.org/debian/"> and
any of its <url name="mirrors" id="http://www.debian.org/distrib/ftplist.html">
in the directory <tt><url name="doc/FAQ/"
id="ftp://ftp.debian.org/debian/doc/FAQ/"></tt>.

<p>The original SGML files used to create this document are also available
in <package/doc-debian/'s source package.

<sect id="documentformats">In what format is this document written?
       
<p>This document was written using the DebianDoc SGML DTD (rewritten
from LinuxDoc SGML). Both LinuxDoc and DebianDoc SGML systems enable
us to create files in a variety of formats from one source, e.g. this
document can be viewed as HTML, text, info, TeX DVI, PostScript or even
PDF.

<p>Conversion utilities for LinuxDoc SGML are called SGML-Tools, and are
available as Debian package <package/sgml-tools/, while the conversion
utilities for DebianDoc SGML are called simply DebianDoc-SGML, and also
available as Debian package, <package/debiandoc-sgml/.

